Mr Unterhalter conceded that there was an obligation\~   in terms of section 13 A(1) read with section 13 A(3) for first respondent to notify and obtain approval of its proposed merger before the merger was implemented.\~   That conclusion clearly\~   followed from the definition of large mergers in section 11 of the Act which provides that \'91for purposes of this Chapter..\'85a large merger means a merger or }{\ul\ulc0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
proposed merger}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 with a value at or above the higher threshold established in terms of sub-section (1)(a)\'92 (my emphasis). First respondent\'92s argument turned on two related\~   issues, namely the time at which first respondent was so obligated to notify and that, at best for appellant, that obligation commenced after completion of the early settlement offer.\~  \~   }
\par \pard\plain \s98{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\cf0\kerning1\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\loch\f0\fs24\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch
