\~  (Case 94/FN/ Nov.00) at p.17: \'91Notification is intended to be as extensive as possible; hence the breadth of the language in section 12. Once a transaction presents the essential features of a merger it is notifiable.\~   If this were not the case, there would be a danger that mergers that might have adverse effects might go undetected because the jurisdictional barriers in terms of section 12, had been set too high.\'92 }
