\par \pard\plain \s98{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\cf0\kerning1\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\loch\f0\fs24\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Section 110of the Canadian Act refers to the acquisition of assets of an operating business where the aggregate value of those assets exceed a certain prescribed threshold.\~   Likewise, section 110(3) refers to the acquisition of voting shares of a corporation that carries on an operating business or controls a corporation that carries on an operating business where the aggregate value of the assets of such business exceed a certain prescribed threshold.\~   Similarly, section 110(6) refers to a proposed acquisition of an interest in the combination that carries on an operating business otherwise than through a corporation (a) where the aggregate value of the assets exceeds a certain prescribed limit.\~   This notification to the Commissioner of Competition is required before the designated transaction is completed.\~   In terms of section 100(1), the Competition Tribunal may issue an interim order forbidding any person named in the application from doing any act or thing that appears to the Tribunal may constitute or be directed towards the }{\ul\ulc0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
completion or implementation }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
of a proposed merger in respect of which an application has not been made\'85\'85\'92 (my emphasis)}
