\par \pard\plain \s98{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\cf0\kerning1\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\loch\f0\fs24\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
That the phrase \'91may not implement a merger until it has been approved\'92 as it appears in section 13 A(3) of the Act does not constitute a complete or impediment, as does section 100 of the Canadian Act, it made it clear by the Tribunal\'92s own finding in }{\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Anglo American Holdings Limited v Kumba Resources Ltd (Industrial Development Corporation intervening) [2003] 2 CPLR 288 (CC) }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
at para 34 where the Tribunal said \'91Whilst one could not expect firms to notify a merger where their ability to require control was at that stage academic it is not necessary for them to have completed the process of acquisition as a jurisdictional prerequisite to notification\'92.\~   In short, the process of investigation begins after notification but not necessarily before the merger has been completed.\~   What section 13 A(3) seeks to prohibit was not the completion of the merger but any implementation thereof prior to authorization having been granted by the relevant competition authorities.}
\par \pard\plain \s98{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\cf0\kerning1\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\loch\f0\fs24\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch
